  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_05_xxvi: Why should imprudent unlearned souls trouble that which is both learned, and ...",
  "body": "Why should imprudent unlearned souls trouble that which is both learned, and prudent? And which is that that is so? she that understandeth the beginning and the end, and hath the true knowledge of that rational essence, that passeth through all things subsisting, and through all ages being ever the same, disposing and dispensing as it were this universe by certain periods of time.",
